Instructions to run the Program:

1. Create a file named query_data.txt in the directory containing the dockerfile and the python codes. This file must contain the number on which the operations are to be run
2. Create a volume mount : docker volume create factors-db
3. Build the container : docker build -t cloud-server .
4. Run the container : docker run -itd --name cloud-server-container --mount type=volume,source=factors-db,target=/vol --mount type=bind,source=/pwd/query_data.txt,target=/tmp/data/query_data.txt -p 65433:65433 cloud-server
5. We need to create a prime_factorization.txt file in the container :
    docker exec -it cloud-server-container sh
    cd ..
    cd vol
    touch prime_factorization.txt
    exit
6. Now proceed to run the data owner and query user files -
    python data_owner.py
    python query_user.py

It can be checked that the prime factorization is appended to the prime_factorization.txt file in the volume mount.
    